<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Item 2.02 Results of Operations and Financial Condition</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On July&nbsp;24, 2015, South State Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;) issued a press release announcing its financial results for the second quarter ended June&nbsp;30, 2015, along with certain other financial information.&#160; A copy of the Company&#146;s press release is attached as Exhibit&nbsp;99.1 to this report and incorporated herein by reference.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Cautionary Note Regarding Any Forward-Looking Statements</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Statements included in this report which are not historical in nature are intended to be, and are hereby identified as, forward looking statements for purposes of the safe harbor provided by Section&nbsp;21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934.&#160; Forward looking statements generally include words such as &#147;expects,&#148; &#147;projects,&#148; &#147;anticipates,&#148; &#147;believes,&#148; &#147;intends,&#148; &#147;estimates,&#148; &#147;strategy,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;potential,&#148; &#147;possible&#148; and other similar expressions.&#160; The Company cautions readers that forward looking statements are subject to certain risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from anticipated results.&#160; Such risks and uncertainties, include, among others, the following possibilities: (1)&nbsp;the outcome of any legal proceedings instituted against the Company; (2)&nbsp;credit risks associated with an obligor&#146;s failure to meet the terms of any contract with the bank or otherwise fail to perform as agreed under the terms of any loan-related document; (3)&nbsp;interest risk involving the effect of a change in interest rates on the bank&#146;s earnings, the market value of the bank&#146;s loan and securities portfolios, and the market value of the Company&#146;s equity; (4)&nbsp;liquidity risk affecting the bank&#146;s ability to meet its obligations when they come due; (5)&nbsp;risks associated with an anticipated increase in the Company&#146;s investment securities portfolio, including risks associated with acquiring and holding investment securities or potentially determining that the amount of investment securities the Company desires to acquire are not available on terms acceptable to the Company; (6)&nbsp;price risk focusing on changes in market factors that may affect the value of traded instruments in &#147;mark-to-market&#148; portfolios; (7)&nbsp;transaction risk arising from problems with service or product delivery; (8)&nbsp;compliance risk involving risk to earnings or capital resulting from violations of or nonconformance with laws, rules, regulations, prescribed practices, or ethical standards; (9)&nbsp;regulatory change risk resulting from new laws, rules, regulations, accounting principles, proscribed practices or ethical standards, including, without limitation, increased capital requirements (including, without limitation, the impact of the capital rules&nbsp;adopted to implement Basel III), Consumer Financial Protection Bureau rules&nbsp;and regulations, and potential changes in accounting principles relating to loan loss recognition; (10)&nbsp;strategic risk resulting from adverse business decisions or improper implementation of business decisions; (11) reputation risk that adversely affects earnings or capital arising from negative public opinion; (12) terrorist activities risk that results in loss of consumer confidence and economic disruptions; (13) cybersecurity risk related to our dependence on internal computer systems and the technology of outside service providers, as well as the potential impacts of third-party security breaches,&#160; subjects the company to potential business disruptions or financial losses resulting from deliberate attacks or unintentional events; (14) economic downturn risk potentially resulting in deterioration in the credit markets, greater than expected non-interest expenses, excessive loan losses and other negative consequences, which risks could be exacerbated by potential negative economic developments resulting from federal spending cuts and/or one or more federal budget-related impasses or actions; (15) greater than expected noninterest expenses; (16) excessive loan losses; (17) failure to realize synergies and other financial benefits from, and to limit liabilities associated with, mergers and acquisitions within the expected time frame; (18) potential deposit attrition, higher than expected costs, customer loss and business disruption associated with merger and acquisition integration, including, without limitation, potential difficulties in maintaining relationships with key personnel and other integration related-matters; (19) the risks of fluctuations in market prices for Company common stock that may or may not reflect economic condition or performance of the Company; (20) the payment of dividends on Company common stock is subject to regulatory supervision as well as the discretion of the board of directors of the Company, the Company&#146;s performance and other factors; and (21) other risks and uncertainties disclosed in the Company&#146;s most recent Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K filed with the SEC or disclosed in documents filed or furnished by the Company with or to the SEC after the filing of such Annual report on Form&nbsp;10-K, any of which could cause actual results to differ materially from future results expressed, implied or otherwise anticipated by such forward looking statements.&#160; The Company undertakes no obligation to update or otherwise revise any forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events, or otherwise.</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SIGNATURES</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit 99.1</font></b></p>
<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<div align="center">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr>
<td width="54%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:54.18%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For Immediate Release</font></p>    </td>
<td width="4%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:4.14%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="41%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:41.66%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Media Contact: Donna Pullen (803) 765-4558</font></p>    </td>   </tr>

<td width="54%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:54.18%;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="41%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:41.66%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Analyst Contact: John Pollok (803) 765-4628</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">South State Corporation Reports Second Quarter Operating EPS of $1.09;</font></b></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Increases Quarterly Cash Dividend</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">COLUMBIA, S.C.&#151;July&nbsp;24, 2015&#151;South State Corporation (NASDAQ: SSB) today released its unaudited results of operations and other financial information for the three-month and six-month period ended June&nbsp;30, 2015.&#160; Highlights of the second quarter 2015 include the following:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Operating earnings improved by $2.4 million to $26.3 million from 1Q 2015, a 10.1% increase</b></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Earnings per share (EPS) &#151; diluted was $1.03 compared to $0.99 in 1Q 2015, a 4.0% increase; and</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>$0.74 in 2Q 2014, a 39.2% increase</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Increased dividend paid to common shareholders by 20.0%; or $0.04 per share since 2Q 2014</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Net income available to the common shareholder of $24.9 million improved by 38.6% from 2Q 2014 of $17.9 million</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Net loan growth (non-acquired loans exceeded acquired loan runoff) during second quarter was $83.8 million or 5.9% annualized</b></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Non-acquired loan growth totaled $202.0 million or 22.6% annualized growth; which</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Outpaced acquired loan runoff of $118.2 million</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Performance ratio improvement 2Q 2015 to 1Q 2015</b></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Operating return on average assets improved to 1.32% from 1.23%</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Operating return on average tangible equity improved to 16.90% from 16.21%</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Efficiency ratio improved to 63.19% from 65.05%</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Operating efficiency ratio improved to 61.22% from 65.05% (excludes merger and conversion expenses)</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Balance sheet and tangible book value improved from 1Q 2015</b></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>OREO decreased $1.1 million to $35.0 million, including the disposition of 58 properties during the quarter</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>FDIC receivable declined to $11.0 million from $16.7 million at end of 1Q 2015</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Noninterest bearing deposits increased by $87.7 million or 20.0% annualized</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Shareholders&#146; equity increased $16.2 million to $1.024 billion</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Tangible equity to tangible assets improved to 8.56% from 8.39%</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Asset quality improvement from 1Q 2015</b></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Nonperforming assets (NPAs) declined by 8.7%, or $6.2 million, to $65.5 million</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>NPAs to total assets improved to 0.81% from 0.89%</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Net charge offs (recoveries) on non-acquired loans were 0.12% in 2Q 2105 up from net recoveries of (0.01%)</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Net charge offs on acquired non-credit impaired loans decreased to 0.18% in 2Q 2015 compared to 0.56%</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Coverage ratio of ALLL on non-acquired non-performing loans improved to 141.0% from 121.6%</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\jms\109185\15-16214-1\task7502815\16214-1-mm-01.htm',USER='109185',CD='Jul 24 08:50 2015' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Quarterly Cash Dividend</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Board of Directors of South State Corporation has declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.25 per share payable on its common stock.&#160; This per share amount is $0.01 per share, or 4.2% higher than the dividend paid in the immediately preceding quarter and is $0.04 per share, or 19.0%, higher than a year ago.&#160; The dividend will be payable on August&nbsp;21, 2015 to shareholders of record as of August&nbsp;14, 2015.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Branch Initiatives - Update</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The consolidation (12) or sale (2)&nbsp;of 14 branches and ATM locations in 2015 during the second, third and fourth quarters is summarized below:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Consolidated eight of the twelve locations during the second quarter (May&nbsp;and June);</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Expect to close or sell the additional six branches during the second half of 2015.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Received all regulatory approvals and anticipate closing on or around August&nbsp;21, 2015 the purchase and assumption of 13 former Bank of America branches (12 in South Carolina and 1 in Georgia).</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>

<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.8%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="8%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:8.0%;">
<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">34.30</font></p>    </td>
<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.8%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="8%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:8.0%;">
<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;font-weight:bold;">34.00</font></b></p>    </td>
<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.8%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;font-weight:bold;">%</font></b></p>    </td>
<td width="8%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:8.0%;">
<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">34.30</font></p>    </td>
<td width="0%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:.98%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">%</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company reported consolidated net income available to common shareholders of $24.9 million, or $1.03 per diluted common share for the three-months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 up from $23.9 million, or $0.99 per diluted common share for the three-months ended March&nbsp;31, 2015.&#160; The $946,000 increase was the result of an increase in interest income of $767,000 (from non-acquired interest income), a decrease in interest expense of $461,000 (no interest expense related to $46.3 million of trust preferred securities and lower time deposit interest expense), an increase in the provision for loan losses of $2.3 million (primarily in the nonacquired loan portfolio), increase in noninterest income of $3.6 million (less amortization of indemnification asset and improvement in most categories of noninterest income), increase in noninterest expenses of $1.0 million (branch consolidation expenses) and an increase in the provision for income taxes of $488,000.&#160; During the quarter, our effective income tax rate remained at 34.00%.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;We continued to make excellent progress in many areas during the second quarter.&#160; Two of our primary objectives this year have been improved efficiency levels and organic growth,&#148; said Robert R. Hill,&nbsp;Jr., CEO of South State Corporation.&#160; &#147;I can report at mid-year that our company has made meaningful strides in these endeavors, and we see many more opportunities for further gains.&nbsp; Our team&#146;s efforts have produced a 39% increase in second quarter earnings this year compared to the same period in 2014.&nbsp; More importantly, we have built strong market share in growing markets that we expect will enable continued growth.&nbsp; I am pleased to announce an additional increase in the cash dividend on common stock to $0.25 per share.&nbsp; This marks our sixth consecutive quarterly dividend increase and is 19% higher than our dividend at this time a year ago.&#148;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>

<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At June&nbsp;30, 2015, the Company&#146;s total assets were $8.1 billion, up from $8.0 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2015 and up $258.8 million from December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; During the second quarter of 2015, the Company experienced asset growth primarily in loans of $83.8 million, excluding the change in the allowance for loan losses, and in investment securities totaling $33.3 million.&#160; During the second quarter, the Company began the process of increasing the investment portfolio as a percentage to total assets and expects this to continue throughout the remainder of 2015.&#160; Mortgage servicing rights asset increased $3.8 million due to an increase in rates and more loans serviced.&#160; Our net deferred tax asset increased $5.3 million primarily from the decline in the deferred tax liability associated with the</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\109194\15-16214-1\task7503075\16214-1-mm-03.htm',USER='109194',CD='Jul 24 12:05 2015' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">smaller unrealized gain in available for sale securities, and from a reclassification of current taxes owed related to prior tax years.&#160; These increases were offset by declines in cash and cash equivalents of $37.4 million; loans held for sale of $14.3 million; FDIC receivable of $5.7 million and OREO of $1.1 million.&#160; Liabilities increased due to noninterest bearing deposit growth of $87.7 million partially offset by decline in interest bearing deposits of $53.8 million.&#160; Fed funds purchased and securities sold under repurchase agreements increased by $11.1 million.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s book value per common share increased to $42.31 per share at June&nbsp;30, 2015, compared to $41.71 at March&nbsp;31, 2015, and $40.78 at December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; Capital increased by $16.2 million due primarily to net income of $24.9 million, which was offset by the common dividend paid of $5.8 million.&#160; Accumulated other comprehensive gain changed to a comprehensive loss during the second quarter 2015, with the decline in the unrealized gains in the AFS securities portfolio during the quarter of $5.1 million, net of tax.&#160; Tangible book value (&#147;TBV&#148;) per common share increased by $0.71 per share to $27.31 at June&nbsp;30, 2015 compared $26.60 at March&nbsp;31, 2015, and increased by $1.72 per share from $25.59 at December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; The quarterly increase was primarily the result of earnings per share of $1.03 during the quarter, offset by the dividend paid to shareholders during the quarter of $0.24 per share.&#160; In addition, tangible equity to tangible assets increased to 8.56% at June&nbsp;30, 2015 up from 8.39% at March&nbsp;31, 2015 and up from 8.28% at December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; At June&nbsp;30, 2014, this ratio was 7.63%.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The total risk-based capital (RBC) ratio is estimated to be 13.7% down from March&nbsp;31, 2015 of 13.8%, due primarily to loan growth and expiration of the commercial loss share agreement at March&nbsp;31, 2015 associated with the CBT transaction from January&nbsp;2010.&#160; Total RBC was also down from December&nbsp;31, 2014 of 14.3%, for the same two reasons above and due to the adoption of Basel III and redemption of $46.3 million of trust preferred securities.&#160; Tier 1 leverage ratio increased slightly from March&nbsp;31, 2015 to 9.6%.&#160; The Company&#146;s capital position remains &#147;well-capitalized&#148; by all measures at June&nbsp;30, 2015.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;During the second quarter, we had $202 million of growth in our non-acquired loan portfolio, which allowed us to achieve approximately $84 million, or 6% annualized, net loan growth,&#148; said John C. Pollok, COO and CFO.&#160; &#147;The improvement in non-interest revenue from all of our business units and the improved operating leverage during the second quarter, have us well-positioned going into the last half of 2015.&#148;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the second quarter of 2015, overall asset quality improved as NPAs declined by $6.2 million, or 8.7% to $65.5 million, and represented 0.81% of total assets.&#160; Compared to June&nbsp;30, 2014, NPAs have declined by $24.3 million, or 27.1%, and represented 1.12% of total assets.&#160; Non-acquired NPAs, excluding acquired loans and acquired other real estate owned (OREO), declined by $3.6 million, or 10.4%, to $30.5 million.&#160; Non-acquired nonperforming loans decreased by $2.9 million, or 10.6%, and non-acquired OREO and other assets repossessed decreased $638,000, or 9.8%.&#160; Non-acquired NPAs as a percentage of total non-acquired loans and repossessed assets declined to 0.80% compared to 0.95% in the first quarter of 2015.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the second quarter, the Company reported $5.3 million in nonperforming loans related to &#147;acquired non-credit impaired loans&#148;.&#160; This was a decrease of $2.1 million from the first quarter of 2015.&#160; Additionally, acquired nonperforming OREO and other assets owned declined by $548,000 million to $29.7 million from March&nbsp;31, 2015 and by $5.8 million from December&nbsp;31, 2014.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At June&nbsp;30, 2015, the allowance for non-acquired loan losses was $34.8 million or 0.92% of non-acquired period-end loans.&#160; The current allowance for loan losses provides 1.41 times coverage of period-end non-acquired nonperforming loans, up from 1.22 times at March&nbsp;31, 2015 and December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; At June&nbsp;30, 2014, this coverage was 1.00.&#160; Net charge-offs (recoveries) within the non-acquired portfolio were $1.1 million, or 0.12% annualized in the second quarter compared to ($54,000) for the first quarter or (0.01%) annualized.&#160; Second quarter 2014 net charge-offs totaled $1.3 million, or 0.17% annualized.&#160; During the second quarter, the allowance for loan losses was increased by $2.4 million compared to a decrease of $1.1 million in the first quarter of 2015 through the provision for loan losses.&#160; The increase was primarily due to larger loans and increases in certain loan types during the second quarter.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\109194\15-16214-1\task7503075\16214-1-mm-03.htm',USER='109194',CD='Jul 24 12:05 2015' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net charge offs related to &#147;acquired non-credit impaired loans&#148; were $533,000 or 0.18% annualized, and the Company recorded a provision for loan losses, accordingly, during the second quarter.&#160; These charge-offs consisted primarily of home equity loans on the coast of South Carolina and other consumer loans.&#160; This was lower than the first quarter 2015 of $1.8 million, or 0.56% annualized net charge offs.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Total OREO decreased by $1.1 million during the second quarter to $35.0 million compared to the first quarter of 2015.&#160; This decline was primarily the result the disposition of 58 properties during the quarter.&#160; Overall, OREO and loan related costs declined by $995,000 compared to the first quarter 2015, and increased by $283,000 compared to the second quarter of 2014.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Net Interest Income and Margin</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">4.75</font></p>    </td>
<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 2.25pt 0in;width:1.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">%</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Non-taxable equivalent net interest income was $82.3 million for the second quarter of 2015, a $1.2 million increase from the first quarter of 2015, resulting primarily from the following:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>A $146.7 million increase in the average balance of non-acquired loans which resulted in an increase in non-acquired loan interest income of approximately $1.4 million; with the yield decreasing to 4.04% during the second quarter from 4.10% in the first quarter; partially offset by</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>A $140.3 million decrease in the average balance of acquired loans from the first quarter of 2015, coupled with a 25 basis point improvement in the yield resulted in a decline in acquired loan interest income of $1.0 million.&#160; The yield improvement on acquired loans from 7.93%, in the first quarter of 2015, to 8.18%, in the second quarter of 2015, was the result of continued improvement in expected cash flows (additional credit releases in 2Q), which results in more loan accretion (income); and</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Interest expense declined by $461,000 from the first quarter of 2015.&#160; This decline was primarily the result of (a)&nbsp;the decrease in interest expense on other borrowings of $204,000, as the second quarter had no interest expense associated with the $46.3 million of trust preferred securities redeemed in early January&nbsp;2015, and (b)&nbsp;the average balance of certificates and other time deposits declined $45.6 million and the rate declined by 5 basis points during the quarter, resulting in a decrease of interest expense of $200,000.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\jms\109185\15-16214-1\task7502815\16214-1-mm-05.htm',USER='109185',CD='Jul 24 08:17 2015' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Tax-equivalent net interest margin decreased 3 basis points from the first quarter of 2015 and was equal to the yield in the second quarter of 2014.&#160; The Company&#146;s average yield on interest-earning assets decreased 5 basis points while the average rate on interest-bearing liabilities decreased 4 basis points from the first quarter of 2015.&#160; During the second quarter of 2015, the Company&#146;s average total assets increased slightly to $8.0 billion from $7.9 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2015 and at December&nbsp;31, 2014.&#160; Average earning assets increased to $7.0 billion up from $6.9 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2015.&#160; Average interest-bearing liabilities remained the same at $5.2 billion for both second quarter of 2015 and first quarter of 2015.&#160; Average non-interest bearing demand deposits increased by $83.7 million during the quarter and by $185.0 million from June&nbsp;30, 2014.&#160; Including the impact of noninterest bearing deposits, the Company&#146;s cost of funds equaled 14 basis points in the second quarter compared to 17 basis points in the first quarter.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Noninterest income was higher than the first quarter of 2015 by approximately $3.6 million to $30.1 million. The increase was the result of the following:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Lower amortization of the FDIC indemnification asset by $1.2 million due to the expiration of the CBT commercial loss share agreement (expect lower amortization in subsequent quarters, however, not as significant as this quarter&#146;s improvement);</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Higher mortgage banking income of $463,000, due primarily to an increased rate environment and higher volume of mortgage loans;</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Higher fees on deposit accounts totaling $1.2 million.&#160; This increase was the result of $719,000&#160; due to increased usage of debit / ATM cards and $511,000 from NSF fees; and</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\109194\15-16214-1\task7503075\16214-1-mm-07.htm',USER='109194',CD='Jul 24 12:08 2015' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Higher recoveries on acquired credit impaired loans of $710,000.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Compared to the second quarter of 2014, noninterest income grew by $5.7 million due to the reduced amortization of the indemnification asset by $3.8 million and improved mortgage banking income of $2.4 million from favorable rate environment and higher volume of loans.&#160; These increases were partially offset by a decline in recoveries of acquired loans of $695,000.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Noninterest expense was $71.5 million in the second quarter of 2015, an increase of $1.0 million from $70.5 million in the first quarter of 2015.&#160; This increase from the first quarter of 2015 was due to $2.2 million of expenses related to branch consolidation during the quarter.&#160; Salaries and benefits were down during the quarter by $1.2 million due primarily to payroll taxes (FICA and unemployment) and an increase in the amount of compensation cost deferred from loan originations.&#160; The company implemented new standard cost deferrals for all loan originations in the second quarter of 2015.&#160; OREO expense and other loan related costs were $995,000 lower than the first quarter.&#160; In the first quarter, the Company auctioned 70 assets in February&nbsp;and the related loss was $640,000, net of indemnification claims.&#160; Other improvements were in furniture and equipment expense, net occupancy, and supplies, printing and postage expense.&#160; These improvements were offset by increases in the following categories:&#160; Information services of $424,000, bankcard expense of $305,000, and other expense of $879,000.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Compared to the second quarter of 2014, noninterest expense improved by $4.4 million primarily with the decline in merger and conversion expense related to merger-branding in 2014 and branch consolidations in 2015.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">South State Corporation will hold a conference call today, July&nbsp;24</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">th</font>; at 11 a.m.&nbsp;Eastern Time during which management will review earnings and performance trends.&#160; Callers wishing to participate may call toll-free by dialing 877-506-9272.&#160; The number for international participants is 412-380-2004.&#160; The conference ID number is 10068054.&#160; Participants can also listen to the live audio webcast through the Investor Relations section of <i>www.SouthStateBank.com</i>.&#160; A replay will be available beginning July&nbsp;24th by 2:00 p.m.&nbsp;Eastern Time until 9:00 a.m.&nbsp;on August&nbsp;7th, 2015.&#160; To listen to the replay, dial 877-344-7529 or 412-317-0088.&#160; The passcode is 10068054.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">***************</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">South State Corporation is the largest bank holding company headquartered in South Carolina. Founded over 80 years ago in 1933, the company&#146;s primary subsidiary, South State Bank, serves the financial needs of its local communities in 19 South Carolina counties, 12 Georgia counties and 4 North Carolina counties.&nbsp;The bank also operates Minis&nbsp;&amp; Co.,&nbsp;Inc. and First Southeast 401K Fiduciaries,&nbsp;Inc., both registered investment advisors; and First Southeast Investor Services,&nbsp;Inc., a limited purpose broker-dealer. South State Corporation has assets of approximately $8.1 billion and its stock is traded under the symbol SSB on the NASDAQ Global Select Market. More information can be found at www.SouthStateBank.com.</font></i></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Non-GAAP Measures</font></i></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Statements included in this press release include non-GAAP measures and should be read along with the accompanying tables which provide a reconciliation of non-GAAP measures to GAAP measures.&#160; Management believes that these non-GAAP measures provide additional useful information.&#160; Non-GAAP measures should not be considered as an alternative to any measure of performance or financial condition as promulgated under GAAP, and investors should consider the company&#146;s performance and financial condition as reported under GAAP and all other relevant information when assessing the performance or financial condition of the company.&#160;&#160; Non-GAAP measures have limitations as analytical tools, and investors should not consider them in isolation or as a substitute for analysis of the company&#146;s results or financial condition as reported under GAAP.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Footnotes to tables:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(</font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">1)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Loan data excludes mortgage loans held for sale.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(2)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">The dividend payout ratio is calculated by dividing total dividends paid during the period by the total net income for the same period.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(3)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Operating earnings, operating return on average assets, and operating return on average equity are non-GAAP measures and exclude the after-tax effect of gains on acquisitions, gains or losses on sales of securities, OTTI, and merger and branding related expense.&#160; Management believes that non-GAAP operating measures provide additional useful information that allows readers to evaluate the ongoing performance of the company.&#160; Non-GAAP measures should not be considered as an alternative to any measure of performance or financial condition as promulgated under GAAP, and investors should consider the company&#146;s performance and financial condition as reported under GAAP and all other relevant information when assessing the performance or financial condition of the company.&#160;&#160; Non-GAAP measures have limitations as analytical tools, and investors should not consider them in isolation or as a substitute for analysis of</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\109194\15-16214-1\task7503075\16214-1-mm-07.htm',USER='109194',CD='Jul 24 12:08 2015' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">the company&#146;s results or financial condition as reported under GAAP.&#160; Operating earnings and the related operating return measures (non-GAAP) exclude the following from net income (GAAP) on an after-tax basis:&#160; (a)&nbsp;pre-tax merger and branding related expense of $4.6 million, $6.8 million, and $6.5 million, for the quarters ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, September&nbsp;30, 2014, and June&nbsp;30, 2014, respectively; (b)&nbsp;branch consolidation expenses of $2.2 million for the quarter ended June&nbsp;30, 2015; and (c)&nbsp;securities gains (losses) of ($90,000) and $88,000 for the quarters ended September&nbsp;30, 2014 and June&nbsp;30, 2014.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(4)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Repossessed assets include OREO and other nonperforming assets.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(5)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Calculated by dividing total non-acquired NPAs by total assets.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(6)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">June&nbsp;30, 2015 ratios are estimated and may be subject to change pending the final filing of the FR Y-9C; all other periods are presented as filed.&#160; All ratios are rounded down to one decimal point.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(7)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">The tangible measures are non-GAAP measures and exclude the effect of period end or average balance of intangible assets.&#160; The tangible returns on equity and common equity measures also add back the after-tax amortization of intangibles to GAAP basis net income.&#160; Management believes that these non-GAAP tangible measures provide additional useful information, particularly since these measures are widely used by industry analysts for companies with prior merger and acquisition activities.&#160; Non-GAAP measures should not be considered as an alternative to any measure of performance or financial condition as promulgated under GAAP, and investors should consider the company&#146;s performance and financial condition as reported under GAAP and all other relevant information when assessing the performance or financial condition of the company.&#160;&#160; Non-GAAP measures have limitations as analytical tools, and investors should not consider them in isolation or as a substitute for analysis of the company&#146;s results or financial condition as reported under GAAP.&#160; The sections titled &#147;Reconciliation of Non-GAAP to GAAP&#148; provide tables that reconcile non-GAAP measures to GAAP.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(8)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Includes noncash loan interest income related to the discount on acquired performing loans of $1.6 million; $1.6 million; $2.3 million; $2.4 million; and $2.2 million, respectively during the five quarters above; and $3.2 million and $5.2 million for the six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015, and 2014, respectively.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:9.0pt;">(9)&#160;&#160; </font><font size="1" style="font-size:9.0pt;">Operating efficiency ratio is calculated by taking the noninterest expense excluding merger cost divided by net interest income and noninterest income excluding securities gains (losses).</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>

<div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Cautionary Statement Regarding Forward Looking Statements</font></i></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Statements included in this report which are not historical in nature are intended to be, and are hereby identified as, forward looking statements for purposes of the safe harbor provided by Section&nbsp;21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934.&#160;&#160; Forward looking statements generally include words such as &#147;expects,&#148; &#147;projects,&#148; &#147;anticipates,&#148; &#147;believes,&#148; &#147;intends,&#148; &#147;estimates,&#148; &#147;strategy,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;potential,&#148; &#147;possible&#148; and other similar expressions.&#160;&#160; The Company cautions readers that forward looking statements are subject to certain risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from anticipated results.&#160; Such risks and uncertainties, include, among others, the following possibilities: (1)&nbsp;the outcome of any legal proceedings instituted against the Company; (2)&nbsp;credit risks associated with an obligor&#146;s failure to meet the terms of any contract with the bank or otherwise fail to perform as agreed under the terms of any loan-related document; (3)&nbsp;interest risk involving the effect of a change in interest rates on the bank&#146;s earnings, the market value of the bank&#146;s loan and securities portfolios, and the market value of the Company&#146;s equity; (4)&nbsp;liquidity risk affecting the bank&#146;s ability to meet its obligations when they come due; (5)&nbsp;risks associated with an anticipated increase in the Company&#146;s investment securities portfolio, including risks associated with acquiring and holding investment securities or potentially determining that the amount of investment securities the Company desires to acquire are not available on terms acceptable to the Company; (6)&nbsp;price risk focusing on changes in market factors that may affect the value of traded instruments in &#147;mark-to-market&#148; portfolios; (7)&nbsp;transaction risk arising from problems with service or product delivery; (8)&nbsp;compliance risk involving risk to earnings or capital resulting from violations of or nonconformance with laws, rules, regulations, prescribed practices, or ethical standards; (9)&nbsp;regulatory change risk resulting from new laws, rules, regulations, accounting principles, proscribed practices or ethical standards, including, without limitation, increased capital requirements (including, without limitation, the impact of the capital rules&nbsp;adopted to implement Basel III), Consumer Financial Protection Bureau rules&nbsp;and regulations, and potential changes in accounting principles relating to loan loss recognition; (10)&nbsp;strategic risk resulting from adverse business decisions or improper implementation of business decisions; (11) reputation risk that adversely affects earnings or capital arising from negative public opinion; (12) terrorist activities risk that results in loss of consumer confidence and economic disruptions; (13) cybersecurity risk related to our dependence on internal computer systems and the technology of outside service providers, as well as the potential impacts of third-party security breaches,&#160; subjects the company to potential business disruptions or financial losses resulting from deliberate attacks or unintentional events; (14) economic downturn risk potentially resulting in deterioration in the credit markets, greater than expected non-interest expenses, excessive loan losses and other negative consequences, which risks could be exacerbated by potential negative economic developments resulting from federal spending cuts and/or one or more federal budget-related impasses or actions; (15) greater than expected noninterest expenses; (16) excessive loan losses; (17) failure to realize synergies and other financial benefits from, and to limit liabilities associated with, mergers and acquisitions within the expected time frame; (18) potential deposit attrition, higher than expected costs, customer loss and business disruption associated with merger and acquisition integrations, and including, without limitation, potential difficulties in maintaining relationships with key personnel and other integration related-matters; (19) the risks of fluctuations in market prices for Company common stock that may or may not reflect economic condition or performance of the Company; (20) the payment of dividends on Company common stock is subject to regulatory supervision as well as the discretion of the board of directors of the Company, the Company&#146;s performance and other factors; and (21) other risks and uncertainties disclosed in the Company&#146;s most recent Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K filed with the SEC or disclosed in documents filed or furnished by the Company with or to the SEC after the filing of such Annual report on Form&nbsp;10-K, any of which could cause actual results to differ materially from future results expressed, implied or otherwise anticipated by such forward looking statements.&#160; The Company undertakes no obligation to update or otherwise revise any forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events, or otherwise.</font></p>
